==Irish==

===Alternative forms===
* {{l|ga|-sean}} {{qualifier|slender form}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|[sˠən̪ˠ]|lang=ga}}

===Suffix===
{{head|ga|suffix|sort=san}}

# [[-self]] {{qualifier|emphatic}}

====Usage notes====
* Added to [[noun|nouns]] in the presence of the [[possessive adjective]] to emphasize the possessor rather than the thing possessed:
*: ''{{l|ga|a}} {{l|ga|carr|gcarr}}'''san''''' -- '''''[[their]]''' [[car]]''
*: ''{{l|ga|a}} {{l|ga|madra|madra}}'''san''''' -- '''''[[their]]''' [[dog]]''
* Added to [[prepositional pronoun|prepositional pronouns]] (ending in a broad consonant) to add emphasis ('''''not''''' to create a reflexive pronoun):
** Used with [[third-person plural]] (except with slender forms such as {{l|ga|dóibh}}; e.g., {{l|ga|acusan}}, {{l|ga|orthusan}}, etc.).
* Added to [[verb|verbs]] to indicate "[[themselves]]":
*: ''{{l|ga|clois|chualadar}}'''san''' -- '''''[[they]] ([[themselves]])''' [[hear|heard]]'' {{context|Munster Irish only|lang=ga}}

====Related terms====
